text: Emmy Schörg (March 1930 – 12 June 2020) was an Austrian stage actress. Schörg was mainly known due to her roles on the in Vienna, where she played for over 40 years. Kurier: Emmy Schörg: Das zeitlose Stegreif-Original. , kurier.at, 13 July 2014 She was born in Vienna. Schörg died on 12 June 2020 in Vienna, aged 90. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Austrian stage actors Category:Actors from Vienna
